%BOM---------------------
Date:4/13/2009 12:28:03 PM
From:Dale Baker
I don't have a legal background but I remember when this question first came
up, I was shocked to find out the ratings agencies were not a regulated part of
the investment advisory world. It's a very stupid system.

Actually there is a case for negligence under the guise of free speech, which
is shouting fire in a crowded theater to stampede the patrons, or any extreme
act deliberately aimed at inciting panic that could lead to damage.

But that would be hard to prove here since the ratings agencies just used
sloppy work to facilitate a bubble. If they had pumped things up then suddenly
changed most of their ratings overnight (or vice versa) then plaintiffs and
prosecutors might look more closely at some kind of action.
