From:Paul Senior
Berkshire: Jurgis Bekepuris has summarized some of my reasons leading to my
negative opinion of BRKB:

http://siliconinvestor.com/readmsg.aspx?msgid=25428441&srchtxt=AAA

My current opinion remains: BRKB is not a value stock. Further, given the size
of the company, its stock's past five-year performance,

http://finance.yahoo.com/q/bc?s=BRK-B&t=5y&l=on&z=m&q=l&c=

and that there seemingly are so many undervalued stocks out there now, many
with high dividend yields (e.g. preferreds), it's difficult for me to see how
BRKA stock can move up to previous highs without also expecting and seeing that
these undervalued companies will also move higher - by multiples. Because so
many better opportunities in stocks seem to me to be available, I say BRKA is
an avoid or short. Of course, jmo.

Dale Baker has the best post I've seen regarding Berkshire now:

"In my 12 years watching BRK, there is always someone who thinks it is
undervalued by 30-40%. It's hard to put a clear value on such a diverse
operation, and whether the market will pay up for that perceived value is
always at issue.

In the last decade, BRKB was a buy under 2500 and a sell over 4000, FWIW."
